RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 74. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEEP MOVIN' ON rated nicely off of the early pace, tracked into the first turn and saved ground into the backstretch run, was guided two then three wide heading to the half-mile pole, stalked the leading pair into the far turn and raced within aim three wide approaching the quarter pole, vied for the lead into the stretch and took a narrow advantage at the furlong grounds, dueled with BABY WAYLON into the final sixteenth, battled with the game runner-up into deep stretch and determinedly won the nod at the finish to prevail. BABY WAYLON away from the gate in good order and was sent to establish the early pace, was engaged by TAMARANDO STAR heading to the first turn and contested the pace with that rival into the backstretch run, disputed decent fractions with TAMARANDO STAR to the half-mile pole, dueled into the far turn and lost a bit of ground at the quarter pole, came again into upper stretch and vied for the lead at the furlong marker, confronted KEEP MOVIN' ON inside of the furlong pole and dueled with that foe to the sixteenth-marker, battled gamely inside of KEEP MOVIN' ON into deep stretch and held a slim lead into the final strides, was bested at the finish and was well clear of the rest for second. TAMARANDO STAR broke alertly and was prominent in the early stages, engaged with BABY WAYLON and contested the pace into the first turn, disputed decent fractions into the backstretch run, dueled with BABY WAYLON into the far turn and took a narrow lead while between horses heading to the quarter pole, battled between runners into the stretch, weakened in the final sixteenth and held safely in the end for third. GROGU allowed to settle, maintained an outside path into the backstretch run, mounted a four wide bid along the far turn, could not sustain that bid into the stretch and flattened out. WE CAN tracked the early pace, raced two wide into the first turn then was guided to the three path into the backstretch run, tracked the decent fractions while not far back heading to the half-mile pole, slipped to the inside into the far turn, was outrun to the quarter pole and did not factor in the stretch. BUTCH O'HARE forwardly placed leaving the start, tracked the early pace two then three wide along the first turn, was well positioned while tracking the pace two wide to the half-mile marker, began to drop back nearing the far turn, was pulled up at the quarter marker and walked off under his own power.

ENTRY.NAME: Tamarando Star
ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5F All Weather Track CR: 63. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALIGRAPHY was outrun in the early stages, built up some momentum through the turn, swung five wide into the stretch and produced a nice rally to get up in time. HARBOR DEAREST came away from the gate running and dueled for the lead with RUNAWAY SALLY through the turn, got the better of that rival passing the five-sixteenths pole, took on a new challenge from SAHARA SUE to the outside, held a short lead at the top of the stretch, got another challenge from HILLSDALE NATION on the inside, was passed briefly by that one near the sixteenths pole but fought back for second. HILLSDALE NATION broke well then was put in a tight hold by the rider, then angled to the inside when clear, stalked the front trio through the turn then tipped out to the two path, quickened stride and gained the show. SAHARA SUE stalked the dueling pacesetters three wide on the turn, got to the flank of HARBOR DEAREST at the top of the stretch, tried hard but could not get by that stubborn foe and was outfinished late for a minor award. RUNAWAY SALLY broke sharply and went head to head with HARBOR DEAREST through the first quarter, came under heavy pressure passing the five-sixteenths marker, remained a factor to mid-stretch then faded in the last furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Runaway Sally
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke sharply, head-to-head duel, under drive 5/16, faded late

ENTRY.NAME: Harbor Dearest
ENTRY.OWNER: Victory Rose Thoroughbreds Inc and Bazzano Richard
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled early, met bids stretch, passed 1/16, fought back

ENTRY.NAME: Caligraphy
ENTRY.COMMENT: outrun early, 5wide stretch rally, was up in time

ENTRY.NAME: Hillsdale Nation
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, stalked inside under stiff hold, quickened stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Sahara Sue
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace duel, bid 3w turn, chased stubborn foe, outfinished

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISCHIEVOUS PIRATE stalked the decent early pace from the inside, was well placed into the turn and saved ground to the quarter marker, angled three wide into the stretch and took command heading to the furlong marker, kicked clear into the final sixteenth and drew away in the late stages. GEORGE HERMAN RUTH allowed to settle early on, chased three wide to the quarter marker, maintained that three wide path into the stretch and gained ground heading to the furlong marker, could not impact the winner in the late stages and outfinished JERSEY BABE in deep stretch to secure second. JERSEY BABE sent leaving the start, contested the early pace two wide and between runners, battled into the turn and took a narrow lead heading to the quarter marker while carving out moderate fractions, was overtaken by MISCHIEVOUS PIRATE heading to the furlong marker, chased the winner into the final sixteenth, weakened in deep stretch, was outfinished for second and held clearly in the end for third. DRUMADOON took back off of the contested early pace, raced four wide into the turn, swung six wide into the stretch, could not impact the top three in the final furlong and passed tiring rivals late. HOGMANAY (IRE) asked for speed leaving the break and contested the early pace from the inside, battled with a trio of rivals into the turn and disputed the moderate pace to the quarter marker, vied for the lead in upper stretch, lost position at the furlong marker, chased into the final sixteenth and faded late. DR. FLASH DANCER prominent to begin and vied for the early lead three wide and between runners, pressed the moderate pace three wide into the turn, lost ground into the stretch and tired. EL CAPRICHO hustled leaving the break and disputed the early pace four deep, maintained that four wide path into the turn and chased to the quarter marker, raced five wide into the stretch, was outrun to the furlong marker and tired in deep stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Mischievous Pirate
ENTRY.OWNER: George Anthony S George Patricia A Isetta Bill Isetta Marilyn and Wall Patty

ENTRY.NAME: Hogmanay (IRE)
ENTRY.OWNER: Little Red Feather Racing Sterling Stables LLC and Naify Marsha

ENTRY.NAME: Jersey Babe
ENTRY.OWNER: Daehling Farms LLC and Tittle Morgan

ENTRY.NAME: George Herman Ruth
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled,chased 3wd turn,no match for winner,closed for 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 95. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DICK BEST broke alertly and set the pace into the first turn, was confronted by CALI CONQUEST and set a contested pace into the backstretch run, conceded the lead heading to the half-mile pole and tracked from the inside into the far turn, was taken off of the rail approaching the quarter pole, swung five wide into the stretch, vied for the lead into upper stretch and took a narrow advantage at the furlong marker, responded to urging into the final sixteenth, drew clear into deep stretch and held sway in the end. SEA OF LIBERTY rated off of the early pace, was floated five wide into the first turn, recovered and tracked the leaders four wide into the backstretch run, pulled on the rider heading to the half-mile marker, made a middle move and rushed to contention three wide approaching the far turn, vied for the lead three wide nearing the quarter marker and battled into upper stretch, was overtaken by DICK BEST at the furlong marker, was outfinished by the winner into the final sixteenth and held well in the end for second. CHIEF JACKSON settled in the second flight to begin and tracked three wide into the first turn, was well positioned into the backstretch run and tracked two wide and between rivals to the half-mile pole, raced three wide into the far turn, gained ground heading to the quarter marker then came in tight and was blocked nearing the top of the stretch, remained in tight at the three-sixteenths marker, found room at mid-stretch, was outkicked into the final sixteenth, stayed on in deep stretch and won the nod for third on the wire. KO SAMUI (IRE) tracked the early pace four wide, drifted out a bit into the first turn and floated out SEA OF LIBERTY, tracked the decent pace three wide through the backstretch run, raced four wide into the far turn and loomed at the quarter marker, vied for the lead into upper stretch and battled to the furlong marker, could not match strides with DICK BEST into the final sixteenth, weakened in deep stretch and just missed for third on the wire. IMPLICITLY tracked the early pace from the inside, came under a tight hold approaching the half-mile marker and navigated traffic to race two wide into the far turn, was boxed in at the quarter pole, continued to be in tight into upper stretch, was able to shake free at the furlong marker but could not muster a late rally. LOVE OF THE SPORT tracked the early pace two wide and between runners into the first turn, advanced into the backstretch run and raced close up to the decent pace while three wide heading to the half-mile marker, took a narrow lead at that station and vied for the lead two wide into the far turn, lost position into the stretch, dropped back approaching the furlong marker and gave way in the final stages. CALI CONQUEST asked for early speed and was prominent into the first turn, engaged with DICK BEST and contested the pace with that rival into the backstretch run, took a narrow lead between runners and vied for the lead heading to the half-mile pole, lost position into the far turn, chased from the inside into upper stretch and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Implicitly
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside,on hold 1/2,boxed in 1/4-1/8,no late rally

ENTRY.NAME: Dick Best
ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,set early pace,took back,swung 5wd 3/16,drew clear late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M All Weather Track CR: 91. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 15 All owed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOLD DAUGHTER away a step slowly from the gate,was kept near the back of the field and saved ground under some restraint through the early stages, tipped out three wide into the stretch, had a little trouble keeping a straight course but kept on under steady handling and got up in time. LA VIKINA was allowed to settle and tracked the front pair traveling well in hand for the first half-mile, was still going easily into the turn, waited until passing the quarter pole to make a move, responded when set down, ran on well, took a short lead inside the sixteenth and was caught yards from the finish. BLUEBERRY MUFFIN was content to cede the lead to PROOF OF JAZZ through the early stages, then decided to press the pace approaching the five furlong marker and pushed that rival to quicken a bit, backed off again and moved back to a stalking position to the far turn, was asked to quicken near the five-sixteenths marker, and took over the lead by the quarter pole, drifted inward down the stretch putting PROOF OF JAZZ in tight quarters, rider lost the crop inside the sixteenth pole and was overtaken in the final yards. PROOF OF JAZZ assumed command away from the start, was able to set comfortable fractions with only a modest bit of pressure on BLUEBERRY MUFFIN, offered no resistance when that foe challenged approaching the stretch, tried to re-rally along the rail but got put in tight quarters and gave way. CHARLOTTE HARBOR fractious in the gate, was unhurried early and lagged near the back of the field to the far turn, set up for a three to four wide run through the turn, then came into the stretch still wide and was only able to pass one in the end. PANDEMIC GIRL tracked the early pace outside of rivals, raced four wide down the backstretch, came under a drive passing the three-furlong pole, struggled to keep up from that point and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Bold Daughter
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow st reserved inside,4wd stretch rally,steady handling,up

ENTRY.NAME: Blueberry Muffin
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked slow pace, bid 5/16, led 1/4, lost crop inside 1/1/6

ENTRY.NAME: Pandemic Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: under drive from 3/8, strugged to keep up,gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: La Vikina
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, well handled, bid 1/4, brief lead, caught late

ENTRY.NAME: Proof of Jazz
ENTRY.COMMENT: seized early lead, set slow pace,in tight stretch,gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Charlotte Harbor
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious gate,unhurried, lagged near back 4wd, no late response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 1M All Weather Track CR: 104. Allowance Purse 33000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAMMAS (GB) forwardly placed in the early going and saved ground into the first turn, tracked the decent pace into the backstretch run and was well placed heading to the half-mile marker, saved all of the ground into the far turn, mounted an inside bid at the quarter marker and took command into the stretch, kicked clear approaching the furlong marker, was kept to task while clear to the sixteenth-pole, dug in in deep stretch and held safely in the end over the oncoming runner-up. I'MGONNABESOMEBODY prominent leaving the start and stalked the early pace two wide into the first turn, raced close up to the decent pace through the backstretch run, pressed MIDNIGHT MAMMOTH into the far turn and vied for the lead three deep at the quarter marker, maintained that three wide path into the lane and chased to mid-stretch, re-rallied into the final sixteenth, pressured LAMMAS in deep stretch but could not get by the determined winner and was second best. ROYAL 'N RANDO allowed to settle and saved ground into the first turn, tracked the decent pace through the backstretch run, saved all of the ground into the far turn and mounted an inside rally into the stretch, needed more in the final furlong but held well for third in the late stages. FREEPORT JOE forwardly placed leaving the start, was a bit keen into the first turn and tracked the leading pair two wide into the backstretch run, was well placed approaching the half-mile marker and was guided three wide into the far turn, mounted a three wide bid at the quarter pole and raced four wide into the stretch, lost ground into the drive and lacked the needed response in the final sixteenth, flattened out and just missed for third on the wire. PASSARANDO unhurried in the early stages and raced outside of his stablemate into the first turn, settled through the backstretch run and chased into the far turn, rallied four wide into the stretch and gained ground at the furlong pole, shifted to the two path approaching the sixteenth-marker, could not muster a final response and finished evenly. MIDNIGHT MAMMOTH sent leaving the break and assumed command in the early stages, dictated terms into the first turn and carved out decent fractions while showing the way to the half-mile pole, came under pressure into the far turn, drifted to the two path at the quarter pole, lost the lead to LAMMAS into upper stretch, dropped back heading to the furlong marker and tired in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Lammas (GB)
ENTRY.OWNER: Charles, Ronald L. and Gordon, Samuel
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside,rail bid 1/4,kicked clear 1/8,dug in late,driving

ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside,rail rally stretch,needed more late,held well 3rd

ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne

ENTRY.NAME: I'mgonnabesomebody
ENTRY.OWNER: Auyeung Nin Crosby Philip Hauck Cheryl McLean Bill Miller Todd Moran Elizabeth a

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 6F All Weather Track CR: 87. Allowance Purse 31000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWALL broke well and was forwardly place from the outset, raced three wide through the turn, was on the outside of a trio contesting the lead at the quarter pole, pulled ahead with a furlong to run and won clear. BREVE lacked early speed and raced at the rear of a compact field, was put into a drive from the five-sixteenths pole, had to alter course to the outside mid-stretch, finished well and surged late to gain second. STRANGE ADDICTION broke well but was unable to keep up with the leading trio early, made some forward progress going into the turn, became boxed in through the turn, tried to go through a narrow opening near the eighth pole, steadied when the hole closed, re-rallied when clear, drifted out a bit into deep stretch, missed for second and was up in time to secure third at the finish. BERRY VALLEY broke well and settled just off the flank of LADY GREGORY and shadowed that foe to the turn, moved up in tandem with SWALL to challenge for the lead approaching the quarter pole, battled to mid-stretch then weakened and was just edged for third. MISS BELLIMBUSTO bumped at the start, was last away and allowed to settle into stride, started making some forward progress passing the five furlong marker, got stuck behind horses through the turn, tried to go through a hole at the top of the stretch at the same time STRANGE ADDICTION went for the same hole, made some contact, neither got through, then shifted to the outside, attempted to rally, but had to check off the heels of STRANGE ADDITION once again yards from the wire. LADY GREGORY broke well and was hustled to the front, pressed by BERRY VALLEY in the early stages, came under pressure at the quarter marker, was overtaken into the stretch, gave way at the eighth pole and faded in the final sixteenth.

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Bellimbusto
ENTRY.OWNER: Jauregui Racing Stables Inc Eplin Danny A Gerson Charles E and Valadez Angel D

ENTRY.NAME: Breve
ENTRY.OWNER: Hanna Mark A Hanna Maria Page Scott Page Cecilia Tootle Herbert Tootle Janet Ven

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 1M All Weather Track CR: 91. Claiming Purse 21000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEED GRAZY was knocked off stride by CHICKENFINGERFRIDAY just after the break causing loss of a length or two at the start, then settled at the rear of the field, remained in that position to the far turn, circled the field to get into contention, came into the stretch five wide with huge momentum but on the wrong lead, sustained the run through the stretch, drifted in late and got a nose in front at the wire. UNION WAVE broke well but eased off the pace to avoid getting hung five wide on the first turn, settled comfortably mid-pack to the half mile pole, moved forward through the far turn but became boxed in, slipped through a successive pair of narrow openings in the stretch, surged up the rail when clear, was put in tight by ARTEMUS GORDON near the sixteenth pole, pushed back and knocked that rival off-stride near the wire causing the rider to stop riding for a couple of strides, got back down and just missed at the wire. ARTEMUS GORDON broke well and got a share of the lead into the first turn, pulled the rider to the front on the backstretch, led the field through reasonable fractions to the far turn, took a short lead at the head of the stretch, got challenged by UNION WAVE to the inside and SPEED GRAZY to the outside inside the furlong grounds, got put in tight at the sixteenth pole, then was bumped off stride by UNION WAVE in the closing yards and lost all chance. EL JOY settled behind early while holding the rail, remained unhurried down the backstretch, awaited room through the turn then got put in tight quarters at the three-sixteenths pole, re-rallied through a narrow opening mid-stretch, ran on and improved position. WODETON (FR) got forward position early and stalked the pacesetter down the backstretch, bid for the lead while racing between horses passing the three furlong pole, was unable to match strides passing the three-sixteenths marker, drifted in some late and weakened in deep stretch. ARREST was sent hard from the break and was able to secure the rail and share of the early lead, then was content to sit just off ARTEMUS GORDON when that one took over the pacesetting duties, tracked inside to the far turn, struggled to keep up from the five-sixteenths pole and finished one-paced. CHICKNFINGERFRIDAY broke in and bumped with SPEED GRAZY after the break, then was outrun into the turn, settled well behind the field to the far turn, tried to rally three wide through the turn ran into some traffic at the head of the stretch swung out a path for room and flattened out. BUTTONWOOD TREE got away well but was forced four wide through the clubhouse turn, stayed out in the clear while racing up close in the early going, made a three wide forward move through the far turn to challenge for for the lead near the five-sixteenths pole then stopped at the head of the stretch and was ridden out to the finish behind the field. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE DEEP STRETCH RUN. IN A MAJORITY DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT SPEED GRAZY DRIFTED IN, CAUSING ARTEMUS GORDON TO STEADY AND TAKE UP IN DEEP STRETCH, AND THIS ACTION COST ARTEMUS GORDON THE OPPORUNTIY OF A BETTER PLACING. SPEED GRAZY WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST AND PLACED THIRD.

ENTRY.NAME: El Joy
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, lacked room turn, in tight 3/16, blkd str, late gain

ENTRY.NAME: Arrest
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent, saved ground, stalked pacesetter, outrun from 5/16
